Spermatheca (
Figure 2c
) — Cervix 4 (3 – 5) long, cup-shaped, with an enlarged atrium.

Previous reports — 

N. aceri

is only known from the West-Palaearctic and Nearctic areas. However, its occurrence in the Nearctic area (three records) might be due to an introduction. Countries from which this species is reported are: 
